    ns1:inpersonHours "28 horas (35.9%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 3.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """Due to the methodological approach of the course as explained in the "Course Description", the teaching activities are an indistinguishable mixture of "theory and practice". It is thus necessary that each student uses his/her laptop in classroom classes.The software needed to follow the course (Chimera, essentially, in addition to multiple web resources) will be presented on the first day of class and consists of programs freely available on the web for academic users, as indicated in the Teaching Resources section. In parallel, students will have to use their own computer tools for file editing, scientific graphics, programming environment (Python) and mathematical analysis.

UPM addresses Sustainable Development Goals (SDG) from an integrated perspective that includes, not only research and innovation initiatives, but also teaching and governance activities within the institution.

UPM's Biotechnology Degree in general, and the subject "Computational Structural Biology For Lead Discovery" in particular, aims to respond to those challenges that the ODS address through the potential applications of the knowledge aquired by the students along their academic formation.

The own scientific nature of the subject "Computational Structural Biology For Lead Discovery" is fully aligned with the following challenge included within UN's SDG initiative : SDG 3 - Health and Welfare: the acquisition of knowledge related to those computational tools useful for the design of new drugs allows the students to gain the ability to address the first development stages of new drugs in order to improve the quality of life of patients undergoing numerous pathological conditions."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Enero"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Septiembre"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Septiembre-Enero"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "33 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description "The course provides an updated view of the computational methodologies for the study of structures and interactions of complexes between receptor biomolecules (mainly proteins) and small molecules or drugs. The course is designed in an interactive way, so students will put into practice in the classroom the computational techniques necessary for the study of these complexes. The course begins with a brief historical review of the field, then the fundamental physicochemical concepts and the sources of information (databases) to be used are introduced. After that, the course will focus on the study of the different techniques used in the drug discovery process. Firstly, the methods used in ligand-based virtual screening are presented, describing the essential concepts of similarity and molecular descriptors at the three levels of analysis (1D, 2D and 3D) together with the methods to calculate the parameters of statistical significance (scoring).Then the course focus on the essential pharmacophore concept and on the techniques of structure-based virtual screening following two complementary approaches: protein-ligand docking and de novo design. At the end of the course, the students will have acquired the computational skills to perform a process to discover a lead compound (i.e., drug design)"@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/maria.garrido%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/maria.garrido%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Biología Estructural Computacional para el Descubrimiento de Dianas"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/CE02> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE02" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Utilizar sistemas operativos, programas y herramientas de uso común en biología computacional, así como, manejar plataformas de cómputo de altas prestaciones, lenguajes de programación y análisis bioinformáticos/ Utilizing operative systems, software and tools commonly used in computational biology, and working with high throughput platforms, programing languages and bioinformatics tools."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/CE03> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE03" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Analizar e interpretar bioinformáticamente los datos que se derivan de las tecnologías ómicas, y proponer soluciones bioinformáticas en relación a dichos datos/ Analyzing and interpreting bioinformatically data derived from ?omics technologies, and proposing bioinformatics solutions according to such data."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/CE05> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE05" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Utilizar herramientas de biología computacional para el análisis genómico, incluida la genómica comparativa y biología evolutiva/ Using computational biology tools for genomics analyses, including comparative genomics and evolutionary biology."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/CE10> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE10" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocimiento de las técnicas de representación del conocimiento reutilizables y modelos de razonamiento en entornos centralizados y distribuidos a utilizar en la resolución de problemas que impliquen conducta inteligente/ Knowing reusable techniques for knowledge representation and reasoning models in centralized and distributed environments, and when to used them for problem solving."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/CG01> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG01" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Poseer los conocimientos que constituyen la base científica y tecnológica de la Biología computacional, lo que permitirá el desarrollo de ideas originales en este campo, en un contexto de investigación o desarrollo/ Having the scientific and technological knowledge in which Computational Biology is based, which will allow the development of original ideas in this field, in the context of both research or development."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/CG03> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG03" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sepan aplicar los conocimientos adquiridos y su capacidad de resolución de problemas en entornos nuevos o poco conocidos dentro de contextos más amplios (o multidisciplinares) relacionados con el area de la Biología Computacional/ Provide students with the ability to apply the acquired knowledge to solve problems in new environments within ample or multidisciplinary contexts in the field of Computational Biology."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/CT02> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT02" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para aplicar el método científico para la resolución de problemas de forma efectiva y creativa/ Capacity to apply the scientific method to solve problems in an efective and creative way."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/RA31> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA31" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Adquirir destreza en el manejo de software para el estudio de estructuras e interacciones en sistemas biomoleculares fármaco"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/RA32> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA32" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocer los fundamentos y el manejo de los métodos de docking y de determinación in silico de sitios de unión y centros activos en proteínas"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000030/2025-26/RA33> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA33" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocer los fundamentos y el manejo de los métodos computacionales para obtener in silico estructuras de biomoléculas, tanto proteínas como fármacos"@es .

